Narrative.p: At St. John's, NL (CYYT), there was an unplanned closure of Runway 11/29 due to a disabled vehicle (Truck 92).

Narrative.p: A Government of Canada, Department of National Defence Lockheed P-3 (Aurora/Orion) (DEMON84) from Greenwood, NS (CYZX) to Greenwood, NS (CYZX) declared an emergency due to a cracked windshield. The aircraft requested clearance to CYZX. No assistance was required. No operational impact. The aircraft landed safely at 1646Z.

RptAircraft.Owner: Government Of Canada, Department Of National Defence
RptAircraft.OperatorName: GOVERNMENT OF CANADA, DEPARTMENT OF NATIONAL DEFENCE

Narrative.p: The transponder of a Government of Canada, Department of National Defence Lockheed C-130 (TSKR343) from Greenwood, NS (CYZX) to Charlottetown, PE (CYYG) cycled through the emergency code. There was no emergency. No impact to operations.
At Wabush, NL (CYWK), the very high frequency omnidirectional range (VOR) 112.3 MHz was unserviceable (U/S). NOTAM issued until November 20th at 2359Z.

RptOccurrence.AerodromeName: GREATER MONCTON ROMEO LEBLANC INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT
RptOccurrence.OccurrenceLocation: GREATER MONCTON ROMEO LEBLANC INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT (CYQM)

Narrative.p: A Moncton Flight College Piper PA-44-180 (C-FHFS) from Moncton/Romeo LeBlanc, NB (CYQM) to Charlottetown, PE (CYYG) departed Runway 24 and performed a right turn without permission.
The Calgary/Springbank, AB (CYBW) tower heard an intermittent emergency locator transmitter (ELT) signal, starting at 2257Z.
A WestJet Encore de Havilland DHC-8-402 (WEN3140) from Edmonton, AB (CYEG) to Calgary, AB (CYYC) conducted an overshoot for Runway 35L due to an indication.

UPDATE from Airworthiness: A Civil Aviation Safety Inspector (CASI) looked into this occurrence. The right-hand (RH) main landing gear (MLG) indicator did not illuminate on approach. The light bulb was replaced and ground tested serviceable.

A Federal Express Airbus A300 (N680FE/FDX241) from Calgary, AB (CYYC) to Memphis, TN (KMEM) was taxiing, turning from Taxiway A to J, and taxied over the southside wigwag when crossing Runway 35L on Taxiway J. The southside wigwag was damaged.
A fax was received indicating that the CYOC community aerodrome radio station (CARS) will be closing early, at 2200Z. A NOTAM was issued.

RptOccEvent.OccEventName: Aerodrome - runway or taxiway surface condition

Narrative.p: The town of Vulcan advised that the runways at Vulcan, AB (CFX6) were closed due to snow. NOTAM issued.
A fax was received requesting a NOTAM for CYOC community aerodrome radio station (CARS) closures on November 11th, 12th, 13th, and 14th, from 2200Z to 0100Z. NOTAM L5230.
An emergency locator transmitter (ELT) went off for approximately 2 seconds at 1539Z. There was another burst of approximately 5 to 10 seconds at 1547Z. Source is unknown. No impact to operations.
The community aerodrome radio stations (CARS) of CYTE, CYCY, CZEM and CYNC did not offer services as published. Impact on operations unknown.
The community aerodrome radio stations (CARS) of CYTE, CYCY, CZEM and CYNC did not offer services as published. Impact on operations unknown.

RptOccEvent.OccEventName: Aerodrome - runway or taxiway surface condition

Narrative.p: At Burwash, YT (CYDB), Runway 11/29 was closed (CLSD) due to snow clearing from 2011162200Z until 2011170200Z.

A Montair Aviation Inc. Cessna 172S (C-GAEM) from Red Deer, AB (CYQF) to Red Deer, AB (CYQF) was observed, on surveillance, inside the zone. Unable to contact the aircraft on 118.5 MHz. The aircraft moved to the west practice area, with no contact, after 2 minutes. No impact on operations.

A Kalitta Charters II Boeing 767-300 (N765CK/CKS9765) from Anchorage, AK (PANC) to Covington/Cincinnati, KY (KCVG) was operating on a different route than that received from the Anchorage (ZAN) air route traffic control centre (ARTCC). Non-conformance monitoring alerted the controller to the discrepancy and the route was corrected in the Canadian Automated Air Traffic System (CAATS).
The Beaver Creek, YT (CYXQ) runway was closed from 2011161736Z until 2011162345Z due to maintenance (MAINT).

After receiving and correctly rereading the standard instrument departure (SID) CYFB5, a Cargojet Airways Boeing 767-323 (C-GXAJ/CJT462) from Iqaluit, NU (CYFB) to Hamilton, ON (CYHM) contacted the air traffic service (ATS) unit and advised that it was at 3600 feet, climbing for 5000 feet, and was proceeding direct 60N072W. The SID recommends a climb to 5,000 feet on the runway centre line. No impact on operations.

The Island Lake, MB (CYIV) mandatory frequency (MF) 122.2 MHz failed at approximately 1550Z. The frequency was NOTAM'd unserviceable until approximately 2359Z. Unable to provide remote aerodrome advisory service (RAAS) at CYIV and St. Theresa, MB (CYST).

RptAircraft.Owner: Government Of Canada, Department Of National Defence
RptAircraft.OperatorName: GOVERNMENT OF CANADA, DEPARTMENT OF NATIONAL DEFENCE

Narrative.p: A Government of Canada, Department of National Defence Lockheed C-130 (Hercules) (ATLS332) went overdue at 1935Z on a VFR flight plan from Calgary, AB (CYYC) and returning to Calgary, AB (CYYC). Flight plan was closed at 2009Z with information obtained from the Kamloops (YKA) flight information centre (FIC).

During descent, a Super T Aviation Cessna 172N (C-FBWG) from Medicine Hat, AB (CYXH) to Medicine Hat, AB (CYXH) reported wind shear on approach to Runway 03. When passing 1000ft above ground level (AGL), the aircraft reported that the wind went from 20 knots to "calm". No impact on operations.

The pilot of a 1740703 Alberta Ltd. Piper PA-31T2 (C-GECD) from La Crete, AB (CFN5) to Edmonton, AB (CYEG) initiated a missed approach, stating they had improper information on the approach (not related to air traffic control). No impact to operations.

Delayed entry as a result of NAV CANADA safety and evaluation quality assurance (QA) review: At La Ronge (Barber Field), SK (CYVC), the power was out at 2159Z. The backup generator did not come on. Backup generator was restored at 2255Z. Power was restored at 2328Z.

A Mountain View Helicopters Robinson R22 Beta (C-FGOK) from Calgary/Springbank, AB (CYBW) to Calgary/Springbank, AB (CYBW) called 8NM Northwest (NW), and was told to enter the zone east of the approach for Runway 17, over 1A highway, at 5000ft. The aircraft entered the zone via the river, then descended without authorization.
At 2330Z, the CYZS community aerodrome radio station (CARS) called to close the station until 2011171500Z, due to weather. A NOTAM (NT) was issued.

Delayed entry as a result of NAV CANADA safety and evaluation quality assurance (QA) review: The Runway 18/36 edge lights at La Ronge (Barber Field), SK (CYVC) failed at 2313Z. The airport manager (APM) was advised. APM installed temporary lights at 0016Z. A NOTAM was issued. No impact to operations.
A St. Thomas Flight Centre Cessna 172N (C-FLHN) reported a laser illumination when 6NM south of Hamilton, ON (CYHM). No operational impact.

RptOccurrence.AerodromeName: TORONTO / LESTER B. PEARSON INTL ON (CYYZ)
RptOccurrence.OccurrenceLocation: TORONTO / LESTER B. PEARSON INTL ON (CYYZ)

Narrative.p: An Air Canada Airbus BD-500-1A11 A220-300 (C-GJXN/ACA260) from Winnipeg/James Armstrong Richardson, MB (CYWG) to Toronto/Lester B. Pearson, ON (CYYZ) initiated a missed approach for Runway 24R due to being "unstable". The aircraft subsequently landed at 1823Z without further incident. No impact on operations.

A Hrycay Consulting Engineers Inc. Cessna 421C (C-GYDM) on an IFR flight from Detroit, MI (KDET) to Windsor, ON (CYQG), inbound from KDET on a visual approach for Runway 25, was issued a landing clearance while a staff vehicle (ST24) was on Runway 25. C-GYDM read back the clearance. Clearance was then immediately cancelled by the controller.

Multiple emergency locator transmitter (ELT) signal reports were received between 1705Z and 1735Z. All details were passed to the Joint Rescue Coordination Centre (JRCC) Trenton, which subsequently advised of an inadvertent ELT activation at Red Lake, ON (CYRL). No impact on operations.

RptOccCategory.OccurrenceCategory: Airprox/TCAS alert/loss of separation/(near) midair collisions

Narrative.p: While the control tower was closed by NOTAM for a mandatory break, a controller witnessed a Journey Air Diamond DA 20-C1 (C-GDME) from Windsor, ON (CYQG) to Windsor, ON (CYQG) taxiing and departing from Runway 25, with a Skylink Express Beech 1900C (SLQ734) from Hamilton, ON (CYHM) to Windsor, ON (CYQG) on final. C-GDME became airborne when the inbound traffic was about 4 miles final. No communications were made by C-GDME on the mandatory frequency. When the tower opened at 1330Z, the controller attempted to make contact with the aircraft twice while the aircraft was in the circuit for Runway 25. Communication was finally established with C-GDME when the aircraft was on final.

A 1582914 Ontario Inc. Diamond DA40 (C-GLBB), on a flight to Wiarton, ON (CYVV), entered the Kitchener/Waterloo, ON (CYKF) control zone 4NM southeast of the field without a clearance. No operational impact.

A Harbour Air de Havilland DHC-6-300 (C-GFHA/HR610) from Victoria Harbour, BC (Water) (CYWH) to Vancouver Harbour, BC (Water) (CYHC) called on the slide, southbound, and after applying power, aborted the take-off slide and advised that they were returning to the dock. No impact to operations.

UPDATE from Flight Operations: A Civil Aviation Safety Inspector (CASI) looked into this occurrence. During application of take-off power, the auto-feather system failed to arm. Take-off was aborted and the aircraft returned to the dock. A micro switch in the auto-feather system was replaced and the aircraft returned to service. No further action required.

RptAcftEvent.AircraftEventName: Flight control systems (ailerons, rudder, rotors, flaps, main, tail)

Narrative.p: A WestJet Encore de Havilland DHC-8-402 (C-FKWE/WEN3107) from Vancouver, BC (CYVR) to Terrace, BC (CYXT) conducted a missed approach procedure for area navigation (RNAV) Runway 33 due to equipment issues. No impact on operations.

UPDATE: Duplicate AOR 269267-V1: A WestJet Encore Ltd. de Havilland DHC-8-402 (C-FKWE/WEN3107) from Vancouver, BC (CYVR) to Terrace, BC (CYXT) declared "PAN PAN" due to no flaps. The Aircraft Rescue and Fire Fighting (ARFF) unit was requested to be on standby at the destination. The aircraft diverted back to CYVR and landed safely at 0358Z. No operational impact. (Duplicate AOR 269267-V1 / CADORS 2020P1813 deleted after information merge)
UPDATE: Duplicate AOR 269285-V1 / CADORS 2020P1822 deleted.

UPDATE from Airworthiness: A Civil Aviation Safety Inspector (CASI) looked into this occurrence. The enterprise reported that after extensive troubleshooting, they found the associated ground studs (9811-GS 117 and 125) to be loose. No further reports of failed or intermittent operation at this time.

A privately registered Cessna 172N from Dawson Creek, BC (CYDQ) to Dawson Creek, BC (CYDQ) was observed to the North (N) of CYDQ, heading inbound. The aircraft entered the CYDQ control zone (CZ) from the North. The specialist tried making contact with the aircraft, but no response was heard. The specialist gave a blind advisory to the aircraft, where they appeared to join the left downwind (LDW) for Runway 25. The specialist requested the aircraft to report when it was off of the runway. A vehicle (ST22) was contacted and advised of the inbound aircraft with intentions unknown, and was told to contact the specialist when the aircraft exited Runway 25 and Taxiway A. The vehicle reported that the aircraft exited Runway 25 and Taxiway A without issue.

RptOccEvent.OccEventName: Aerodrome - runway or taxiway surface condition

Narrative.p: Due to snow, Tumbler Ridge, BC (CBX7) was closed.
A Carson Air Ltd. Beech B300 (C-GRXX/CRN911) from Kelowna, BC (CYLW) to Dawson Creek, BC (CYDQ) rejected its takeoff on Runway 34.

At Castlegar/West Kootenay, BC (CYCG), a snow blower (BW120) broke down on the threshold of Runway 33. The departure of a Carson Air Beech B300 (CRN911) from Castlegar/West Kootenay, BC (CYCG) to Vancouver, BC (CYVR) was delayed by 15 minutes for removal of BW120.

RptOccCategory.OccurrenceCategory: Airprox/TCAS alert/loss of separation/(near) midair collisions

Narrative.p: An unknown aircraft on a 1200 code was observed on radar flying around the Langley, BC (CYNJ) control zone, at varying altitudes, for about 10 minutes. The CYNJ tower asked pilots for reports, as there were multiple conflicts with other aircraft in the zone. The unknown aircraft was observed leaving the CYNJ control zone and landing at Delta/Delta Heritage Air Park, BC (CAK3).

A Skyquest Aviation Ltd. Piper PA-34-200 (C-GTYH) from Langley, BC (CYNJ) to Langley, BC (CYNJ) entered the Abbotsford, BC (CYXX) control zone without clearance, multiple times, from 1900Z until 1916Z. A Swoop Inc. Boeing 737-8CT
(WSW407) from Abbotsford, BC (CYXX) to Toronto/Lester B. Pearson, ON (CYYZ) was briefly delayed on departure.

A Southern Interior Flight Centre Cessna 172S (C-GPWR) from Penticton, BC (CYYF) to Kelowna, BC (CYLW) entered Taxiway B and crossed the hold line for Runway 16/34 without contacting the flight service station (FSS). A Cessna 172 aircraft was in the circuit. C-GPWR departed before impacting the circuit traffic. No impact to operations.

RptOccCategory.OccurrenceCategory: Airprox/TCAS alert/loss of separation/(near) midair collisions

Narrative.p: The pilot of an Airsprint Inc. Cessna 525A (C-FIAS/ASP511) from Vancouver, BC (CYVR) to Penticton, BC (CYYF) executed a missed approach on area navigation (RNAV) Z 16 at CYYF due to a terrain warning. C-FIAS conducted a second approach and landed safely. No impact on operations.

An Air Canada Boeing 787-9 (C-FVNB/ACA854) from Vancouver, BC (CYVR) to London/Heathrow, United Kingdom (EGLL) reported a bird strike while departing from Runway 26L. The remains of a widgeon were recovered. Runway 26L re-opened at 0245Z. The aircraft continued to its destination.

A Propair Inc. Beech A100 (PRO4210) from Rouyn-Noranda, QC (CYUY) to La Grande-4, QC (CYAH) returned to land at CYUY after taking off towards CYAH. No reason specified. The aircraft took off at 1702Z, and landed at 1810Z. No impact.

At Matagami, QC (CYNM), the dial-up remote communications outlets (DRCOs) 123.55 MHz and 126.7 MHz were unserviceable (U/S) when the station was checked. The Technical Operations Coordinator (TOC) was advised (ADZ). NOTAM issued. Unknown impact on operations. Update: on November 09, 2020 (201109), at 1305Z, technical (TECH) operations requested to make requests with aircraft (ACFT) in the sector in order to assess the return to service.

Narrative.p: Runway 07-25 at Rimouski, QC (CYXK) was closed on November 16, 2020 from 0400Z to 1310Z due to weather. NOTAM issued. Unknown impact.
